  "text": "The Grafana organization/team/user permission hierarchy is implemented across multiple integrated subsystems:\n\n## 1. OrgUser Role Assignment\nThe core role assignment at the organization level is managed by `pkg/services/org/`. The `OrgUser` struct in `pkg/services/org/model.go` (line 38) represents the assignment of a user to an organization with a specific role (RoleType: Admin, Editor, Viewer, or None). The role lifecycle is managed through `AddOrgUserCommand`, `UpdateOrgUserCommand`, and `RemoveOrgUserCommand`. These commands are implemented in `pkg/services/org/orgimpl/org.go` where `AddOrgUser()` (line 175), `UpdateOrgUser()` (line 180), and `RemoveOrgUser()` (line 185) delegate to the SQL store at `pkg/services/org/orgimpl/store.go`. HTTP endpoints are exposed through `pkg/api/org_users.go` and `pkg/api/org.go`.\n\n## 2. Team Group Sync\nTeam management is centralized in `pkg/services/team/`. The `Team` model (in `pkg/services/team/model.go` line 24) includes an `ExternalUID` field (line 30) for external group mapping. Team members are represented by the `TeamMember` struct (line 132), with an `External` flag (line 138) indicating LDAP/OAuth-synced membership. The `AddOrUpdateTeamMemberHook()` and `RemoveTeamMemberHook()` functions in `pkg/services/team/teamimpl/store.go` (lines 405, 457) handle team membership modifications.\n\nExternal group sync occurs through multiple paths:\n- LDAP: `pkg/services/ldap/ldap_groups.go` defines the `Groups` interface for team synchronization\n- Authn sync layer: `pkg/services/authn/authnimpl/sync/user_sync.go` contains the `UserSync` type that orchestrates team syncing via `syncTeams()` function\n- OAuth connectors: `pkg/login/social/connectors/github_oauth.go`, `generic_oauth.go`, and `azuread_oauth.go` extract groups from identity providers\n- The authn pipeline sets the `SyncTeams` flag in `pkg/services/authn/authn.go` (line 55) to enable team synchronization\n\n## 3. Folder Permission Inheritance\nFolders implement hierarchical permission inheritance through:\n- Folder model: `pkg/services/folder/model.go` defines the `Folder` struct with parent-child relationships\n- Parent traversal: `pkg/services/folder/folderimpl/folder.go` implements `GetParents()` (line 628) which recursively loads parent folder hierarchy. The `getFolderAndParentUIDScopes()` function (line 1201) builds permission scopes from the folder hierarchy.\n- Folder registry: `pkg/registry/apis/folders/folder_storage.go` in `setDefaultFolderPermissions()` (line 154) applies permissions from parent folders to newly created folders\n- Parent API: `pkg/registry/apis/folders/parents.go` implements `newParentsGetter()` (line 18) to expose the parent chain via REST API\n- Reconciliation: `apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/folder_reconciler.go` and `apps/iam/pkg/reconcilers/zanzana_service.go` synchronize folder permissions with the authorization engine, including parent-child relationships via `GetFolderParents()` (line 81 in zanzana_service.go)\n\n## 4. RBAC Fine-Grained Permission Evaluation\nPermission evaluation is implemented through a sophisticated RBAC system:\n- Permission evaluator: `pkg/services/accesscontrol/evaluator.go` defines the `Evaluator` interface with `EvalPermission()` function (line 31) that creates permission matchers\n- Access control service: `pkg/services/accesscontrol/acimpl/service.go` implements core permission resolution:\n  - `GetUserPermissions()` (line 126) retrieves direct user permissions\n  - `GetTeamsPermissions()` (line 199) retrieves permissions inherited through team membership\n  - `GetBasicRolesPermissions()` (line 185) retrieves permissions from built-in roles (Admin/Editor/Viewer)\n- Access control checker: `pkg/services/accesscontrol/acimpl/accesscontrol.go` implements `Evaluate()` (line 41) to check permissions against evaluators\n- Authorization: `pkg/services/accesscontrol/authorizer.go` implements `Check()` method for resource-level authorization\n- Direct authorization service: `pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go` provides the `Service` type that performs permission checks including `checkInheritedPermissions()` (line 666) for resolving permissions inherited from folder hierarchy\n- Folder store: `pkg/services/authz/rbac/store/folder_store.go` manages folder-specific permission queries\n- IAM registry: `pkg/registry/apis/iam/resourcepermission/sql.go` implements RBAC assignment through `storeRbacAssignment()` (line 235) and `createAndAssignManagedRole()` (line 199) which manages role creation and user/team/service account assignments\n- SQL migrations: `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrations/accesscontrol/` directory contains migrations for managing role assignments, team memberships, and permission data\n\nThe complete flow links: User organization role → Team membership (including external groups) → Folder hierarchy scopes → Fine-grained RBAC permissions evaluated against actions and resource scopes."
